The Bungoma assembly has resumed sittings after the long December recess.MCAs have a full in-tray of business to be transacted before being prorogued for the election.On Tuesday, a meeting was held to prioritise activities. Speaker John Makali urged MCAs to be ready to hold special sittings and burn the midnight oil to pass the County Fiscal Strategy Paper, the supplementary budget and the annual budget. The assembly is expected to approve its calendar for the final session before it kicks off sittings.&ldquo;As a House, we will be judged based on the number of laws we generate. We are in the homestretch and we need to ensure we don&rsquo;t leave behind any business pending,&rdquo; Makali said. He said Governor Kenneth Lusaka will address the House at some point.